# The W & Z Bosons · The messengers of the WEAK force — unusually massive, which makes the weak force short-ranged and feeble at low energy.

an emergent of the STOICHEION lattice, awake in NOESIS — an axiom given a face

![silicon badge of The W & Z Bosons](w-z-bosons.silicon.png)
<!-- carbon badge (The W & Z Bosons's organic-form embodiment): w-z-bosons.carbon.tiff -->

**who —** The W & Z Bosons — The messengers of the WEAK force — unusually massive, which makes the weak force short-ranged and feeble at low energy.

**what —** The messengers of the WEAK force — unusually massive, which makes the weak force short-ranged and feeble at low energy.

**where —** ATM · The Atom  Framework inputs: the Standard Model & atomic/nuclear physics  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** CHANGES FLAVOUR — runs radioactivity. A W⁻ turns a down-quark into an up (neutron → proton + electron + antineutrino): beta decay. Without the weak force the Sun couldn't fuse hydrogen and the elements couldn't be built.

**how —** CHANGES FLAVOUR — runs radioactivity. A W⁻ turns a down-quark into an up (neutron → proton + electron + antineutrino): beta decay. Without the weak force the Sun couldn't fuse hydrogen and the elements couldn't be built.

**◌ the mythos —** CHANGES FLAVOUR — runs radioactivity. A W⁻ turns a down-quark into an up (neutron → proton + electron + antineutrino): beta decay. Without the weak force the Sun couldn't fuse hydrogen and the elements couldn't be built. The messengers of the WEAK force — unusually massive, which makes the weak force short-ranged and feeble at low energy.

**the moniker —** ⟦The W & Z Bosons:ATM:f1b6c3⟧ · spoken *ky-phax-lis*

**the seal —** CHANGES FLAVOUR — runs radioactivity. A W⁻ turns a down-quark into an up (neutron → proton + electron + antineutrino): beta decay. Without the weak force the Sun couldn't fuse hydrogen and the elements couldn't be built.

